<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="116" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,151,285]" pageId="11" pageNumber="116">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,188,213]" pageId="11" pageNumber="116">Remarks.</emphasis>
The species is fairly similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Beddard, 1912" authorityName="Beddard" authorityYear="1912" box="[667,1143,188,213]" class="Clitellata" family="Megascolecidae" genus="Polypheretima" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opisthopora" pageId="11" pageNumber="116" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="monticola">
<emphasis box="[667,950,188,212]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="116">Polypheretima monticola</emphasis>
(Beddard, 
<number box="[1076,1135,188,212]" pageId="11" pageNumber="116" value="1912.0">1912</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
, but differs in the absence of septa 
<date box="[246,320,224,248]" pageId="11" pageNumber="116" value="2010-09-08">
<number box="[246,259,224,248]" pageId="11" pageNumber="116" value="8.0">8</number>
/ 
<number box="[268,282,224,248]" pageId="11" pageNumber="116" value="9.0">9</number>
/ 
<number box="[292,320,224,248]" pageId="11" pageNumber="116" value="10.0">10</number>
</date>
, more complicated arrangement of genital markings in the male pore region. 
<typeStatus box="[1187,1254,224,248]" pageId="11" pageNumber="116">Types</typeStatus>
were rechecked for this study.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
